   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Gaussian chain segmental distribution\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 269,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from scipy import integrate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 270,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "R=1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 271,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "3.154962962962964"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 271,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "4*np.pi*(1.1e-6)**3/3/(4*np.pi*(0.75e-6)**3/3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 272,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "epsi=np.linspace(0,1,20)\n",
    "x=(3*epsi**2-3*epsi+1)\n",
    "y=(3*epsi**2-3*epsi+1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 273,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0, 0.5, 'amplitude')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 273,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#plt.plot(epsi,x)\n",
    "plt.plot(x,1/y,'.')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('variance')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('amplitude')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Unperturbed Gaussian Chain"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 309,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "r=np.linspace(-2,2,1000)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 310,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "R=1\n",
    "f = lambda x,r: np.exp(-2*r**2/(2*R**2*(3*x**2-3*x+1)))/(3*x**2-3*x+1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 311,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dens=[]\n",
    "for p in r:\n",
    "    y, err = integrate.quad(f, 0, 1, args=(p,))\n",
    "    dens.append(y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 312,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7f8282a37b50>]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 312,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.semilogy(r,dens)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 313,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from scipy.optimize import curve_fit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 314,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def gfit(x,*args):\n",
    "    amp = args\n",
    "    n=50\n",
    "    var_range=np.linspace(0.3,1,n)\n",
    "    y=0\n",
    "    for i,var in enumerate(var_range):\n",
    "        y=y+amp[i]*np.exp(-x**2/(2*R**2*var))/var\n",
    "    return(y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 315,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n=50\n",
    "var_range=np.linspace(0.3,1,n)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 316,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "params = 1/np.linspace(0.3,1,n)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "fitted_params,_ = curve_fit(gfit,r, np.array(dens), p0=params)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 317,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {

      ]

   ],

    "fitted_params"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    "plt.plot(var_range,np.abs(fitted_params))\n",

    "plt.ylabel('amplitudes')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
